com.wizarpos.devices.msr
Interface MSROperationResult

All Superinterfaces:
OperationResult
public interface MSROperationResult
extends OperationResult

MSROperationResults are generated by the Magnetic Stripe Reader device implementation to notify the application of the completion of a requested operation.

The getStatus() method inherited from OperationResult is used to retrieve the success of the operation. Constants are defined in OperationResult for that purpose.

A second set of constants is defined starting in OperationResult and continued in this interface. These constants begin with "ERR_" and supply supplemental information via getInfo() when a status of EVT_ERROR is returned by getStatus().

Field Detail

ERR_READFAIL

static final int ERR_READFAIL
Encoded media was detected, but was unable to be read. Data was not recovered for any track. This constant may be returned by getInfo() if the readData completion event status is EVT_ERROR.
